Police said they had arrested 20 suspects terrorising residents of Sabon Birni Local Government Area and its environs in Sokoto State. The state Commissioner of Police, Mr. Ibrahim Kaoje, who made this known at a news conference yesterday in Sokoto, said the suspects were arrested in the last seven days. Kaoje said the suspects were arrested by a joint security team, which comprised the police, Army, Customs, the Department of State Services (DSS), Immigration, Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), among others. He said the suspects were apprehended with a gun, axes, Army uniforms, hemps and drugs as well as items suspected to be charms. Kaoje called on the residents to assist security operatives with useful information that would lead to the arrest of criminals in their domains. The commissioner urged the people to go about their businesses as security agencies had taken control of the black spots in the state. Police yesterday arrested about 20 suspected hoodlums terrorising residents of Ketu, Mile 12 in Kosofe area of Lagos State.   They were arrested after a raid of the area by operatives of Ketu Police Division. The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), CSP Chike Oti, who confirmed the arrests, said… In "Metro and Crime" A military and police task force operation in Taraba State on Wednesday led to the killing of 10 suspected herdsmen, believed to have been terrorising Taraba and Adamawa states. The Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP) in charge of Operations, Falaye Olalayi, flanked by the Brigade Commander, 23 Army Brigade, Yola,… In "Metro and Crime" Police have arrested a man, Usman DanMaliki, of Rikina village in Dange Local Government Area of Sokoto State for pretending as a policeman and extorting money from the public. Parading the suspect, the state Commissioner of Police, Alhaji Murtala Usman Mani, said DanMaliki conspired with SheShe Baba, now at large,… In "Metro and Crime"